			<tr><td colspan="2">
				<div class="postbody">
				I hate firewalls because they generate calls to tech support from people who don't know how to configure them  and wonder why they cannot connect to the internet after they click no to every popup that reads "Do you want to allow internet explorer to access the internet" DOH!
<br />

<br />
Oh sorry, off the tech rant now...
<br />
Doesn't really matter where you place the firewall if you're just trying to protect your stuff from outsiders. One thing to remember though is if someone really wants to get in and has the knowledge, they can circumvent even the best firewall. Security holes are found every day. Patches come out, new holes are found.
<br />
If you are concerned with prying eyes on your LAN or risk of someone getting beyond your router, install the firewall on each pc.  Otherwise, just the router without the firewall feature enabled is probably fine. 
<br />
Again, people who really want to get in probably can no matter what you do.<br />
				<span class="gensmall"></span><br />
				</div>
			</td></tr>
